headline: S&P Global (SPGI) Margins Improve, Reinforcing Bullish Narratives Despite Valuation Concerns
summary: S&P Global (SPGI) reported EPS growth of 20.7% over the past year, well above its five-year average of 7.9%. Net profit margins improved to 27.3% from last year’s 25%. Despite this strong performance, shares trade at $491.57, notably above the estimated fair value of $294.28, and the company’s Price-To-Earnings Ratio of 37.4x remains a premium against industry peers. The combination of consistent profit growth, expanding margins, and high-quality earnings is keeping sentiment upbeat. However,...
